subSubSection.paragraph:
Female (see 
Fig. 7B
): This species can be distinguished from the others in the genus by the following combination of characters: Scutal area III with two small acuminate tubercles; proapical apophysis of coxa IV long (smaller than males), straight and acuminate (apex more rounded than males); femur IV without DBA, armed with seven rows of spines (in a different pattern than males); coloration like in males.
